OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776874270
OL,3,CDriver, 69, guilty of killing Take
OL,4,CThat fan on her way to Bristol gig
OL,6,FA driver has been found guilty of
OL,7,Fkilling a pedestrian who was on her
OL,8,Fway to a Take That concert in Bristol.
OL,10,FFiona Hodge, a retired social worker
OL,11,Ffrom St Werburghs, was found guilty of
OL,12,Fcausing the death of Donna Crossman,
OL,13,F53, after a week-long trial at Bristol
OL,14,FCrown Court.
OL,16,FJurors heard that Hodge was driving
OL,17,Falong the A370 Brunel Way into Bristol
OL,18,Fon the afternoon of 9 June in 2024
OL,19,Fafter a walk in the Mendips with
OL,20,Ffriends when she hit Donna Crossman.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
