FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776874270
OL,3,CDriver, 69, guilty of killing Take
OL,4,CThat fan on her way to Bristol gig
OL,6,FHodge told Bristol Crown Court she had
OL,7,F"no recollection" of the moments
OL,8,Fleading up to the crash and has since
OL,9,Fbeen diagnosed with epilepsy by
OL,10,Fneurologists.
OL,12,FMs Crossman was walking towards the
OL,13,Fstadium with her friends when a car
OL,14,Fbeing driven by Hodge mounted the
OL,15,Fpavement and hit her, knocking her off
OL,16,Fthe bridge.
OL,18,FThe victim, from Bridgend in Wales,
OL,19,Fwas taken to Southmead Hospital but
OL,20,Fdied of her injuries the following day.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776874270
OL,3,CDriver, 69, guilty of killing Take
OL,4,CThat fan on her way to Bristol gig
OL,6,FThe jury heard evidence from a world-
OL,7,Fleading epilepsy expert, Professor
OL,8,FSimon Shorvon, who said it was 70-80%
OL,9,Flikely that Hodge had suffered a
OL,10,F'complex partial seizure' when driving
OL,11,Falong Brunel Way.
OL,13,FFiona Hodge had accepted she had been
OL,14,Fresponsible for Donna Crossman's
OL,15,Fdeath, but pleaded not guilty to a
OL,16,Fsingle charge of causing death by
OL,17,Fcareless driving on the grounds of
OL,18,Finsanity; a legal defence for
OL,19,Fsuffering an epileptic episode behind
OL,20,Fthe wheel.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,433,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F432A1776874270
OL,3,CDriver, 69, guilty of killing Take
OL,4,CThat fan on her way to Bristol gig
OL,6,FBut the jury reached its verdict that
OL,7,Fshe was guilty of causing Donna
OL,8,FCrossman's death by careless driving.
OL,10,FA number of witnesses gave evidence
OL,11,Fduring the trial, including friends of
OL,12,Fthe defendant, and two independent
OL,13,Fwitnesses who were driving on the same
OL,14,Froad and saw a car 'swerving between
OL,15,Flanes' in front of them.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
